House passed Financial CHOICE Act cultivates Main Street economic growth by removing roadblocks to access to capital from local institutions
House passed Financial CHOICE Act - alleviates the crushing burdens placed on our rural communities by Dodd-Frank https:// davidyoung.house.gov/media-center/w eeklyreport/better-choice-iowans …
Our local and smaller institutions didn't cause the financial collapse of 2008. But Dodd-Frank's one-size-fits-all approach punishes them.
Dodd-Frank makes local banks in towns like Glenwood & Creston follow same regs and rules as those applied to JPMorgan Chase in New York.
Dodd-Frank forced Main Street to live under the same crushing regulations of Wall Street - gave folks fewer choices & lacked accountability
Dodd-Frank made big banks bigger limited Iowans’ access to capital, raised bank fees, made mortgages more expensive https:// davidyoung.house.gov/media-center/w eeklyreport/better-choice-iowans …
Dodd-Frank dumped mountains of costly rules & regulations on hardworking Iowans forcing thousands of hometown banks to close their doors.
Dodd-Frank Act was written with the intention of protecting consumers but created nightmares for community banks & local credit unions.
